## Research on this pattern
The feedback pattern was last user tested in September 2020. The following findings were reported:
{{
    onsList({
        "itemsList": [
            {
                "text": 'users prefer to give feedback at the end of a questionnaire or survey, rather than be interrupted during it'
            },
            {
                "text": 'users do not expect to use the feedback form to report technical issues they are having with the service'
            },
            {
                "text": 'if the feedback call to action is placed alongside a call to action for another optional process, such as getting a confirmation email, it should also be displayed at the end of that process'
            },
            {
                "text": 'users do not expect a reply to the feedback they give, but they want to know how it will be used'
            },
            {
                "text": 'the content of the feedback success message must not appear too “automated” as this gives the impression that the user’s feedback will not be looked at'
            }
        ]
    })
}}

